<br>
It behooves anyone leading a raid to find out as much background information about the encounter as available.  The end game is about equipping your members so they can progress at whatever rate your resources allow.  A solid strategy is just another resource to that end. <br>
<br>
Will TWC be there with milk, cookies and a blanket ready to pat ToN’s back if they wipe 20 times coming up with there own wacky Fennin strategy?  Doubt it, but I’m sure some among them will start another self-righteous post about ToN using “leet HnE strats” if they get him on their first try.<br>
<br>
If I were in ToN leadership I’d pump Tadd and Miriai for as much information as possible.  Heck, I’d have Tadd MT once she’s a member as she’s still the #2 equipped warrior on the server.  Once a recruit becomes a member it’s silly to hold them to a double standard.  Then again my goal would be progression, not huggles with TWC.  <br>
<br>
There are methods to progression everyone should consider cheating (like killing a 1% mob, bind rushing, buying your mt ebay, etc) but using the best strategy available isn’t among them.<br>
